    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is experiencing a BSOD (Blue Screen of Death) with the stop code \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\". They want me to investigate this using enterprise root cause analysis and provide a fixability score. They also want to know about their PC temperature and component health.\n\nSince this is a system diagnostic task, I should:\n1. First, try to gather more information about their system\n2. Check for Windows Event Logs that might have more details about the BSOD\n3. Look for any minidump files that might contain the crash dump\n4. Provide an analysis of the WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\n\nThe web search failed, but I know from my knowledge that WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR is a Windows Hardware Error Architecture error that typically indicates a hardware problem. Common causes include:\n- CPU overheating or unstable overclocking\n- RAM issues\n- Power supply problems\n- Motherboard issues\n- GPU problems\n\nLet me check their system's event logs and see if there are any minidump files. I'll use PowerShell commands to gather this information.",
      "timestamp": 1783146359413
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"Get-WinEvent -LogName System -MaxEvents 50 | Where-Object { $_.Id -eq 41 -or $_.Id -eq 6008 -or $_.Message -like \\\"*WHEA*\\\" -or $_.Message -like \\\"*bugcheck*\\\" } | Select-Object -First 10\", \"description\": \"Check Windows Event Log for BSOD events\"}",
